# Unix / Linux / macOS crontab recipe for the daily kickoff.
#
# Install with:  crontab -e   (then paste an edited copy of the line below)
# List with:     crontab -l
#
# Requirements (see ../README.md):
#   - CONTENT_HOME must be set for the command (cron does NOT load your shell profile,
#     so set it inline on the line — that is what the leading assignment does).
#   - Replace <CONTENT_HOME>, <NODE_BIN>, <ENGINE_DIR>, and the HH:MM time.
#
# Fields:  minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week  command
# Example below runs every day at 08:30 host-local time.

30 8 * * *  CONTENT_HOME=<CONTENT_HOME> <NODE_BIN> <ENGINE_DIR>/bin/engine.js kickoff >> <CONTENT_HOME>/logs/kickoff.cron.log 2>&1

# Notes:
#   - Logs append to $CONTENT_HOME/logs/kickoff.cron.log; the engine redacts secrets at
#     write time, but rotate/secure this file like any operational log.
#   - Drop `--now` for the scheduled morning-kickoff trigger; add it only for an
#     on-demand manual run.
#   - cron uses the system timezone; align HH:MM with your calendar's scheduler.timezone.
